The paper discusses a new learning paradigm for Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) algorithms, specifically in the context of high-dimensional visual decision making domains with discrete action spaces. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). However, given that the paper focuses on improving DRL algorithms, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of Atari 2600 as a benchmark also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.CV. The mention of decomposing a control policy into independent components suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.RO and cs.SY.
